<%- include('partials/header', { title: 'How FirstQA Works' }) %>

<div class="container py-5">
  <h1 class="text-center mb-5">How FirstQA Works</h1>
  
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-8 mx-auto">
      <div class="card shadow-sm mb-5">
        <div class="card-body p-5">
          <h2 class="mb-4">The Process</h2>
          
          <div class="d-flex mb-4">
            <div class="me-4">
              <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="width: 50px; height: 50px;">
                <h3 class="mb-0">1</h3>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3>Install the GitHub App</h3>
              <p>Begin by installing the FirstQA GitHub App to your repositories. This gives us the necessary access to receive notifications about your pull requests.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="d-flex mb-4">
            <div class="me-4">
              <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="width: 50px; height: 50px;">
                <h3 class="mb-0">2</h3>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3>Request Testing</h3>
              <p>When you have a pull request that needs manual testing, simply comment <code>/test</code> on the PR. Our system will automatically detect this command and create a test request.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="d-flex mb-4">
            <div class="me-4">
              <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="width: 50px; height: 50px;">
                <h3 class="mb-0">3</h3>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3>We Test Your PR</h3>
              <p>Our expert testers will review your PR, set up the necessary environment, and thoroughly test the changes according to best practices and your specific requirements.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          
          <div class="d-flex">
            <div class="me-4">
              <div class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center" style="width: 50px; height: 50px;">
                <h3 class="mb-0">4</h3>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h3>Get Detailed Results</h3>
              <p>Once testing is complete, we'll post a detailed report directly to your PR with our findings, including any bugs discovered, screenshots, and recommendations.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <div class="card shadow-sm">
        <div class="card-body p-5">
          <h2 class="mb-4">What We Test</h2>
          
          <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li class="list-group-item py-3">
              <h5><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i> Functionality</h5>
              <p class="mb-0">We verify that your changes work as expected across various scenarios.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item py-3">
              <h5><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i> User Experience</h5>
              <p class="mb-0">We evaluate the user experience and flow, highlighting any usability issues.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item py-3">
              <h5><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i> Cross-Browser Compatibility</h5>
              <p class="mb-0">We test your changes across major browsers to ensure consistent behavior.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item py-3">
              <h5><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i> Mobile Responsiveness</h5>
              <p class="mb-0">For web applications, we verify proper rendering and functionality on mobile devices.</p>
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item py-3">
              <h5><i class="bi bi-check-circle-fill text-success me-2"></i> Edge Cases</h5>
              <p class="mb-0">We look for unusual scenarios that might cause issues in production.</p>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<%- include('partials/footer') %> 